.TH cmerge 1 "" "cportage @cportage_VERSION@" cportage
.SH "NAME"
cmerge - \fBemerge\fR(1) compatible commandline package manager
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.TP
.BR cmerge
[\fIglobal options...\fR] \fIaction\fR ...
.TP
.BR cmerge
\fB--help\fR | \fB--info\fR | \fB--version\fR
.TP
.BR cmerge
[\fB--install\fR] [merge options] [--] <atom>
.TP
.BR cmerge
\fB--depclean\fR | \fB-c\fR [merge options] [--] <atom>
.TP
.BR cmerge
\fB--unmerge\fR | \fB\-C\fR [merge options] [--] <atom>
.TP
.BR cmerge
\fB--search\fR | \fB-s\fR [--] <something>
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Command-line frontend to \fBcportage\fR(3)
.SH "ACTIONS"
.TP
.BR "No action"
No action is treated as \fB--install\fR
.TP
.BR "--help"
Show this manpage
.TP
.BR "--info"
Produce a list of information to include in bug reports
.TP
.BR "--version"
Output cportage version
.SH "GLOBAL OPTIONS"
.TP
.BR "\fB--verbose\fR | \fB-v\fR | \fB--quiet\fR | \fB-q\fR"
Controls output verbosity
.SH "MERGE OPTIONS"
.TP
.BR "\fB--pretend\fR | \fB-p\fR"
Instead of actually performing any action, only display what would be done
.SH "ENVIRONMENT OPTIONS"
See \fBcportage\fR(3)
.SH "AUTHORS"
.nf
Marat Radchenko <marat@slonopotamus.org>
.fi
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR cportage (3),
.BR ebuild (5),
.BR make.conf (5),
.BR portage (5)
